1
00:00:00,650 --> 00:00:02,210
<i>Previously on Prison Break...</i>

2
00:00:02,313 --> 00:00:04,004
Hey, yo, we're headed out man.

3
00:00:04,908 --> 00:00:05,904
Good luck.

4
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:07,812
I hope you find the girl, buddy.

5
00:00:07,851 --> 00:00:09,156
Baby, what the hell is going on?

6
00:00:09,179 --> 00:00:12,310
Yeah, well Hector says
that you can serve your full sentence.

7
00:00:12,370 --> 00:00:14,172
What are you doing here,
where's Maricruz?

8
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:15,252
She's with me now.

9
00:00:15,619 --> 00:00:17,710
What's this I hear about you
coming home soon?

10
00:00:17,829 --> 00:00:20,084
You're not getting your daughter's
hopes up, are you?

11
00:00:20,111 --> 00:00:21,369
<i>You sitting down?</i>

12
00:00:21,644 --> 00:00:23,370
Your man is coming home this week.

13
00:00:23,561 --> 00:00:25,676
We can make it to the courthouse
on foot from here.

14
00:00:25,690 --> 00:00:28,070
You don't understand,
everything is in that car.

15
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:30,960
I've been clean for 18 months now.

16
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:34,310
I want to help people get
from where I've been to where I am.

17
00:00:38,198 --> 00:00:41,080
You were right. I should never have
gotten you involved in this.

18
00:00:41,270 --> 00:00:42,689
I just need to know

19
00:00:43,190 --> 00:00:46,805
what Michael scofield wanted from you
in exchange for the green card.

20
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:48,689
<i>Caroline, I've been doing this
for 15 years</i>

21
00:00:48,766 --> 00:00:50,867
and it's never been about
anything other than you,

22
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:53,317
your family and,
most importantly, this country.

23
00:00:53,550 --> 00:00:55,510
Now, I need to know
who I'm working for here.

24
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:57,720
You are working for me.

25
00:00:57,993 --> 00:00:59,588
Are you aware of any arrangement

26
00:00:59,627 --> 00:01:03,140
officer Bellick had with any inmate
regarding prison industries?

27
00:01:03,303 --> 00:01:04,950
Yeah, he sold it to John Abruzzi.

28
00:01:05,470 --> 00:01:08,950
Officer Brad Bellick, you're terminated,
effective immediately.

29
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:12,070
<i>They just announced
the rewards on the TV.</i>

30
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:13,552
How much?

31
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:16,050
<i>$100,000 a piece.</i>

32
00:01:16,491 --> 00:01:20,067
The money is just outside
of Tooele, Utah.

33
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,216
<i>I got the man! He's on the wall!</i>

34
00:01:24,171 --> 00:01:25,232
Truck!

35
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:32,363
Get men in all the area hospitals.

36
00:01:32,401 --> 00:01:34,422
Wherever they are,
one of them is bleeding good.

37
00:01:34,446 --> 00:01:35,469
We got to move.

38
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:36,759
I can't.

39
00:01:42,678 --> 00:01:45,090
You put in all that work,
break out of prison,

40
00:01:45,206 --> 00:01:47,262
only you end up dead
at the bottom of a ditch.

41
00:01:48,057 --> 00:01:49,272
Kind of sad really.

42
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,547
So which one of them was it?

43
00:01:54,470 --> 00:01:58,486
12 HOURS EARLIER (del vo)

44
00:02:03,755 --> 00:02:05,484
We've got a blanket
on all the hospitals.

45
00:02:05,607 --> 00:02:06,620
Free clinics?

46
00:02:06,810 --> 00:02:09,519
If they've got band-aids and bactine,
we've got a body in there.

47
00:02:09,740 --> 00:02:11,188
The brothers come in for medical,

48
00:02:11,246 --> 00:02:13,613
they're getting it in a van
on the way back to Fox River.

49
00:02:13,614 --> 00:02:15,120
Anything break on the other six?

50
00:02:15,664 --> 00:02:18,181
Eyes and ears on the families.
So far, no hits.

51
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:19,652
Maybe just laying low.

52
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:22,050
What's the hardest thing
in the world for a con to do?

53
00:02:22,420 --> 00:02:23,420
Nothing?

54
00:02:23,478 --> 00:02:25,988
- Few things in life are certain, Ms...
- Lang.

55
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,138
Death, taxes and the fact
that a man on the run

56
00:02:28,196 --> 00:02:30,960
will make a mistake sometime
in the first 72 hours.

57
00:02:30,980 --> 00:02:33,881
Needing distance, he'll steal a car.
Needing money, he'll rob a store.

58
00:02:34,091 --> 00:02:36,811
Needing help, he'll trust
someone that he shouldn't.

59
00:02:37,358 --> 00:02:38,640
And when he does...

60
00:02:39,090 --> 00:02:41,709
he will leave behind the crumbs
that will take us right to him.

61
00:02:48,679 --> 00:02:49,800
I need your help.

62
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:51,176
Michael, what are you doing here?

63
00:02:51,203 --> 00:02:52,542
Cayenne pepper.

64
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:53,655
What?

65
00:02:55,148 --> 00:02:56,691
In your kitchen, do you have any?

66
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,060
Yeah, maybe.

67
00:02:59,577 --> 00:03:01,255
I'm gonna need some rubbing alcohol,

68
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:04,110
some towels and pain killers,
whatever you got.

69
00:03:04,130 --> 00:03:05,460
And some booze.

70
00:03:05,510 --> 00:03:06,580
Please!

71
00:03:12,826 --> 00:03:15,970
Easy, easy, easy, easy.

72
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:22,450
it's fine, man, let's just keep moving.

73
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:25,910
We keep moving
and that leg keeps bleeding.

74
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:29,180
The leg keeps bleeding
and we're not getting out of Illinois.

75
00:03:29,324 --> 00:03:30,385
This is going to hurt.

76
00:03:32,230 --> 00:03:35,280
That's good, that's good, that's good.

77
00:03:37,391 --> 00:03:39,110
This will seal the capillaries.

78
00:03:39,810 --> 00:03:41,533
Michael, you should not have come here.

79
00:03:41,572 --> 00:03:43,340
The police have been here
asking questions.

80
00:03:43,378 --> 00:03:44,362
We didn't have a choice.

81
00:03:44,420 --> 00:03:47,049
Listen, you know I'm thankful
for the help with the green card,

82
00:03:47,062 --> 00:03:49,077
- but I just don't wanna get involved.
- I know.

83
00:03:49,091 --> 00:03:51,111
Iit wasn't part of our deal,
I know, I know.

84
00:03:51,210 --> 00:03:54,449
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

85
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:56,171
But there was nowhere else to go.

86
00:03:56,390 --> 00:03:58,700
When I saw you on the news,
I was worried.

87
00:03:59,210 --> 00:04:01,340
I just hoped you'd crossed
the border by now.

88
00:04:02,130 --> 00:04:03,283
So did I.

89
00:04:06,790 --> 00:04:08,210
Keep giving him these.

90
00:04:08,881 --> 00:04:10,849
See if you can find him
some clean clothes.

91
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:13,997
I got to go back and get our car.

92
00:04:14,623 --> 00:04:17,536
Forget the car. We can get another.

93
00:04:17,710 --> 00:04:19,790
I don't need a car, I need that car.

94
00:04:19,853 --> 00:04:20,900
Why?

95
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:25,343
Because in that car...

96
00:04:25,693 --> 00:04:28,023
everything we need to disappear.

97
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:10,154
What have you got?

98
00:05:10,192 --> 00:05:13,530
Here we go boss, one of the blues
hauled in a vagrant a couple hours ago.

99
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,953
Seems the man was in possession
of an item or two

100
00:05:15,992 --> 00:05:17,690
that didn't exactly belong to him.

101
00:05:29,313 --> 00:05:31,030
Looks like we got our first mistake.

102
00:06:15,071 --> 00:06:17,200
Hey, you got any of that oriental jerky?

103
00:06:17,590 --> 00:06:18,660
Excuse me?

104
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,070
Teriyaki flavor.

105
00:06:23,908 --> 00:06:25,520
You got any in the back?

106
00:06:27,693 --> 00:06:28,720
Let me check.

107
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:30,898
And, uh, give me a bottle
of that Early Times

108
00:06:30,899 --> 00:06:32,199
while you're back there, junior.

109
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:35,288
Feel free to earn your paycheck today.
Watch the store, I'll be right back.

110
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:43,513
How goes it, Roy?

111
00:06:54,570 --> 00:06:57,333
To be honest, Roy, I could've done
without the knee to the junk.

112
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,280
You beat me, Brad.

113
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,307
Like a little girl, you beat me.

114
00:07:01,365 --> 00:07:02,620
Well, you had it coming.

115
00:07:02,870 --> 00:07:04,110
Yeah, probably did.

116
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:09,310
You know it's crazy, us taking it out
on each other for how things turned out.

117
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:10,700
You want someone to blame,

118
00:07:10,730 --> 00:07:14,110
how about those convicts staring up
at us from the papers every morning.

119
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,530
They took my job,

120
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:18,470
my pension,

121
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:20,730
my dignity.

122
00:07:20,890 --> 00:07:23,897
When they went over that wall,they took
all of it right along with them.

123
00:07:23,974 --> 00:07:25,990
Everything I worked for my whole life.

124
00:07:27,345 --> 00:07:29,120
Did you see that reward they got?

125
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:32,899
Those ass-hats are worth more dead
than you and I are alive.

126
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,340
Not for long.

127
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,610
What do you mean?

128
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:38,620
I mean somebody's going to get
that money, might as well be me.

129
00:07:42,010 --> 00:07:43,757
You know a job like that might

130
00:07:43,845 --> 00:07:46,220
go a little smoother with
an extra pair of hands.

131
00:07:46,290 --> 00:07:48,800
You really think I'm going
to split that reward with you?

132
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:52,150
I'm just saying, you run into
those brothers,two of them, one of you.

133
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:55,210
You might find yourself
wishing for a good wingman.

134
00:08:10,110 --> 00:08:11,490
Just get it done, Mike.

135
00:08:14,170 --> 00:08:15,070
How are you doing?

136
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,200
May I help you?

137
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:18,880
Yeah, I hope so, Chuck.

138
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:21,850
I think you may have towed my car.

139
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:23,780
What did it look like?

140
00:08:23,818 --> 00:08:24,940
<i>What did it look like?<i>

141
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:28,500
The car you stole the backpack from.
What did it look like?

142
00:08:29,227 --> 00:08:31,909
I don't know, man, maybe it was gray.

143
00:08:32,010 --> 00:08:33,520
It's a gray Accord.

144
00:08:34,262 --> 00:08:35,265
License number?

145
00:08:35,323 --> 00:08:36,713
Look, man, that's all I know.

146
00:08:36,940 --> 00:08:38,690
I wasn't after the car.

147
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:41,230
Thought the bag had some clothes in it.

148
00:08:41,596 --> 00:08:43,324
You remember where the car was parked?

149
00:08:43,363 --> 00:08:44,462
Where'd you park it?

150
00:08:45,258 --> 00:08:46,900
Corner of Hancock and 15th.

151
00:08:47,016 --> 00:08:49,499
I don't know, maybe around
15th somewhere,

152
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,820
but it ain't going to be there anymore.

153
00:08:52,379 --> 00:08:53,382
What do you mean?

154
00:08:53,401 --> 00:08:57,684
That's the reason I didn't get to grab
anything else. Tow truck rolls up.

155
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,100
Already on it.

156
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:06,080
It's going to be 60 bucks for the tow,
and 24 for the overnight.

157
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:22,166
All right, be right back
with your vehicle.

158
00:09:22,264 --> 00:09:23,692
Shouldn't take but a few minutes.

159
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:36,160
<i>- Hello? - Petey, it's Sucre.

160
00:09:36,556 --> 00:09:38,391
<i>As in, Fernando Sucre?</i>

161
00:09:38,665 --> 00:09:39,870
Is there another one?

162
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:40,905
<i>Man, I hope not.</i>

163
00:09:40,980 --> 00:09:43,979
But my boy Sucre would not
be calling me on the telephone,

164
00:09:43,999 --> 00:09:47,855
thereby making me an accessory
to his dumb-ass escape, man.

165
00:09:47,990 --> 00:09:49,930
I- I'm sorry, bro, I just...I just...

166
00:09:49,950 --> 00:09:52,190
I just need you to get a hold
of Maricruz.

167
00:09:52,269 --> 00:09:55,105
I can't call her cell because the Feds
will be all over the place...

168
00:09:55,163 --> 00:09:58,180
homie, listen, man, you have got
to forget about that girl.

169
00:09:58,350 --> 00:10:00,228
If I could forget about her, pendejo,

170
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:03,259
I'd still be at Fox River, sitting
in cell 40 on your old bunk.

171
00:10:03,371 --> 00:10:05,705
Yeah, well, I hope you're holding on
to something tight

172
00:10:05,706 --> 00:10:07,817
'cause I'm about to break it down
for you, brother.

173
00:10:07,856 --> 00:10:10,610
She's getting married to Hector
on Saturday.

174
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,300
What day is today?

175
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:15,610
Thursday, bro. Sorry, man.

176
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:22,663
All right, you got to get her
to your place

177
00:10:23,143 --> 00:10:24,357
- tonight.
<i>- Hang on, man...</i>

178
00:10:24,396 --> 00:10:26,800
I got one last shot to make her
change her mind, dude.

179
00:10:27,631 --> 00:10:29,734
Just find a way to get her there, okay?

180
00:10:29,850 --> 00:10:31,460
Wait... Sucre, hang on, man.

181
00:11:05,612 --> 00:11:06,880
And...

182
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:08,528
about the broken window.

183
00:11:08,586 --> 00:11:10,878
We got a disclaimer
posted right there on the wall...

184
00:11:10,916 --> 00:11:14,710
I don't...I don't... I don't care about
the broken window, Chuck.

185
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:18,750
I had a backpack inside.

186
00:11:20,008 --> 00:11:21,262
Not when we got it.

187
00:11:22,030 --> 00:11:23,810
I got some paperwork
for you to fill out.

188
00:11:28,905 --> 00:11:30,210
You look familiar.

189
00:11:33,930 --> 00:11:34,980
Yeah, you...

190
00:11:35,030 --> 00:11:38,410
you were the attending
when I first started here.

191
00:11:38,790 --> 00:11:39,770
Sure.

192
00:11:41,512 --> 00:11:44,460
Would one of you mind
calling me a cab, please?

193
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,570
I don't think so.

194
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:50,250
Look, dr. Tancredi, I...

195
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:53,090
I just want to say good luck.

196
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,770
- Sara Tancredi?
- I'm sorry.

197
00:11:54,810 --> 00:11:56,412
You have the right to remain silent.

198
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:58,303
Please place your hands
behind your back.

199
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,767
If you have any questions,
I'm happy to come...

200
00:12:00,768 --> 00:12:04,120
Ms. Tancredi, out of respect for
your father, I'm going to ask you again.

201
00:12:04,350 --> 00:12:05,490
My father?

202
00:12:05,710 --> 00:12:09,160
I'm sure he'd prefer that
this went without incident.

203
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:10,922
You have the right
to speak to an attorney

204
00:12:10,923 --> 00:12:12,530
before you speak to the police.

205
00:12:12,650 --> 00:12:15,580
Anything you say may be used
against you in a court of law.

206
00:12:16,422 --> 00:12:19,509
And to have an attorney present
during questioning now or in the future.

207
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:23,220
Caroline, they're taking her in.

208
00:12:24,945 --> 00:12:26,681
Of course. I'll keep an eye on her.

209
00:12:29,602 --> 00:12:32,090
All you got to do is sign here
at the bottom,

210
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:34,184
and be on your way.

211
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:36,210
Excuse me, please.

212
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:39,632
Brewster's towing.

213
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:42,238
This is agent Mahone with the F.B.I.

214
00:12:42,296 --> 00:12:43,473
Who am I speaking with?

215
00:12:44,409 --> 00:12:45,392
Chuck.

216
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:47,832
Okay, Chuck, I want to alert you
to a possible situation.

217
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:49,231
Are you listening to me, Chuck?

218
00:12:49,245 --> 00:12:51,864
<i>An individual may be coming there
to inquire about a vehicle.</i>

219
00:12:51,941 --> 00:12:54,750
<i>A gray Accord, probably
with a busted rear window.</i>

220
00:12:54,780 --> 00:12:58,060
Has anyone come by looking for a vehicle
that matches that description?

221
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:04,850
Yes, sir.

222
00:13:05,390 --> 00:13:06,387
When?

223
00:13:11,488 --> 00:13:13,013
Will you tell me when he was there?

224
00:13:15,691 --> 00:13:17,080
Right now.

225
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:25,893
Brewster's towing. Scofield's there.

226
00:13:25,990 --> 00:13:27,070
Chuck, stall him.

227
00:13:27,121 --> 00:13:28,228
- Stall him.
- Scofield,

228
00:13:28,247 --> 00:13:31,080
- the I.D.?
- Don't let him leave, okay?

229
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:32,534
It's my supervisor, he's, he...

230
00:13:32,930 --> 00:13:35,384
I just got to get clearance
before I can release the car.

231
00:13:37,310 --> 00:13:38,350
<i>Chuck, you there?</i>

232
00:13:38,575 --> 00:13:39,540
<i>Hey, Chuck!</i>

233
00:13:39,559 --> 00:13:41,700
Okay, come on, come on,
Chuck, you still with me?

234
00:13:43,914 --> 00:13:47,656
Yeah, that vehicle might not be here
when you get here.

235
00:13:48,310 --> 00:13:50,100
You need to send somebody now.

236
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,820
Do not let him leave!

237
00:13:55,010 --> 00:13:56,162
Oh, he got the keys.

238
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:02,460
Where the hell are those units?

239
00:14:02,610 --> 00:14:04,270
Still six or seven minutes out, sir.

240
00:14:10,370 --> 00:14:13,290
We got chatter. It's Franklin.
He's at a payphone downtown.

241
00:14:13,870 --> 00:14:15,170
Mistake number two.

242
00:14:17,353 --> 00:14:18,430
Look, I know.

243
00:14:18,490 --> 00:14:20,755
I know, baby, just let me explain,
all right?

244
00:14:21,245 --> 00:14:23,040
Were you ever even in the military?

245
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:25,990
I served my country,
and my country served me up.

246
00:14:26,611 --> 00:14:27,614
All right?

247
00:14:27,692 --> 00:14:31,170
Now, look, I wish I could lay this
all out for you right here, right now.

248
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:34,780
<i>But just know, baby, I am sorry,
and I love you,</i>

249
00:14:35,378 --> 00:14:37,890
<i>and when the time comes,
I will explain everything.</i>

250
00:14:39,310 --> 00:14:43,300
Give me one good reason why
