- Nope.

508
00:32:20,995 --> 00:32:22,630
Maybe he didn't get your message.

509
00:32:32,767 --> 00:32:34,110
They've stopped.

510
00:32:34,780 --> 00:32:36,704
Couple miles up ahead. There's...

511
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:38,893
There's nothing up there. What...?

512
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:40,700
What are they waiting on?

513
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:42,834
Or who?

514
00:32:48,463 --> 00:32:50,890
All right, that's good,
that's good, that's good.

515
00:33:12,691 --> 00:33:14,046
Oh, come on.

516
00:33:14,607 --> 00:33:15,880
Come on!

517
00:33:18,490 --> 00:33:19,498
Go red.

518
00:33:20,021 --> 00:33:21,434
Now, go red!

519
00:33:48,340 --> 00:33:49,680
Just one more thing.

520
00:33:51,870 --> 00:33:53,220
Do you trust me?

521
00:33:55,760 --> 00:33:56,998
Of course.

522
00:33:57,820 --> 00:33:59,864
How do you throw
the hunter off the scent?

523
00:34:00,710 --> 00:34:02,062
Get rid of the prey.

524
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:04,344
Remember,

525
00:34:04,460 --> 00:34:07,905
once I hit scan, we'll have about
30 seconds before it reaches 103.7.

526
00:34:07,990 --> 00:34:09,296
And then she blows?

527
00:34:09,614 --> 00:34:11,395
That's right. Ready?

528
00:34:11,530 --> 00:34:12,686
Yeah.

529
00:34:31,578 --> 00:34:32,895
All right, let's go.

530
00:34:37,661 --> 00:34:38,725
Wait,

531
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,889
The music is not changing.

532
00:34:41,370 --> 00:34:42,960
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

533
00:34:44,010 --> 00:34:45,370
Something's wrong.

534
00:34:46,260 --> 00:34:47,546
What happened?

535
00:34:47,980 --> 00:34:49,101
I don't know.

536
00:34:49,449 --> 00:34:51,520
But we're going to need the explosion.

537
00:34:54,740 --> 00:34:55,973
He's here.

538
00:35:06,612 --> 00:35:08,218
The radio must have jammed.

539
00:35:08,580 --> 00:35:10,719
We're going to have
to set it off manually.

540
00:35:10,770 --> 00:35:12,534
The car could blow any second, Michael.

541
00:35:12,592 --> 00:35:15,083
Well, the feds are going
to be here in about two minutes.

542
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:17,560
If it doesn't look like
we're dead, we will be.

543
00:35:18,078 --> 00:35:19,646
Rock, paper, scissors?

544
00:35:20,170 --> 00:35:21,919
- Linc?
- It's my turn.

545
00:35:38,591 --> 00:35:40,330
Better pray for reception.

546
00:35:48,978 --> 00:35:52,690
How many stations
between 102. 1 and 103.7?

547
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:54,705
Way out here?

548
00:35:55,420 --> 00:35:57,122
Just one, probably.

549
00:36:35,454 --> 00:36:36,906
Where's Maricruz?

550
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:39,384
- Hey, look, man...
- No, no, Petey. You look.

551
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:41,571
I haven't slept in 72 hours,

552
00:36:41,649 --> 00:36:44,049
I've seen a man's hand
get chopped off, I've been...

553
00:36:44,050 --> 00:36:46,382
I've been shot at, dug up a grave,

554
00:36:46,479 --> 00:36:48,520
stolen a car,
jumped on a fricking a train,

555
00:36:49,206 --> 00:36:51,019
so please, just tell me where she is.

556
00:36:51,020 --> 00:36:53,219
Hey, Fernando, slow down, man.

557
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:55,799
I was trying to tell you,
but you hung up the phone, man.

558
00:36:55,959 --> 00:36:57,546
The wedding, it's in Vegas.

559
00:37:00,090 --> 00:37:01,109
The city?

560
00:37:01,197 --> 00:37:03,616
Yeah, and they left a few hours ago.

561
00:37:13,788 --> 00:37:15,389
Wait, no, no. No, no, no.

562
00:37:15,390 --> 00:37:17,590
Come on, hey, come on. Fernando!

563
00:37:17,830 --> 00:37:19,229
It's pristine, man. It's just...

564
00:37:19,230 --> 00:37:21,340
gonna be back to you
in one piece, I promise.

565
00:37:21,417 --> 00:37:23,360
Can we go back
to the part where I said no?

566
00:37:23,627 --> 00:37:24,947
I wish I had another choice.

567
00:37:25,083 --> 00:37:27,329
You do have a choice. Come on, man.

568
00:37:27,330 --> 00:37:30,525
It's a 1952 Ural motorbike, bro.

569
00:37:30,564 --> 00:37:32,910
- If you so much as scratch it...
- No scratches...

570
00:37:33,340 --> 00:37:34,709
I promise.

571
00:37:37,210 --> 00:37:38,943
She's the love of my life, bro.

572
00:37:40,370 --> 00:37:41,676
I got to do something.

573
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:43,340
You look like hell.

574
00:37:43,590 --> 00:37:45,166
I've been through hell, papi.

575
00:37:45,550 --> 00:37:48,318
Now I just got to get to Vegas.

576
00:37:57,977 --> 00:37:59,893
Hi, I'm Sara, and I...

577
00:38:08,238 --> 00:38:10,115
over the years, I've worked with...

578
00:38:11,030 --> 00:38:14,600
more than a few people
who had a history of addiction, and...

579
00:38:16,521 --> 00:38:19,433
I would tell them that I could
understand what they were going through,

580
00:38:19,446 --> 00:38:20,411
because I...

581
00:38:21,469 --> 00:38:25,301
used to be just like them.
I used to be an addict, too.

582
00:38:26,250 --> 00:38:27,282
And I think...

583
00:38:30,370 --> 00:38:33,370
I think that what's becoming
clear to me is that...

584
00:38:34,703 --> 00:38:36,420
the reason I understood them is...

585
00:38:36,650 --> 00:38:38,123
because I am like them.

586
00:38:41,350 --> 00:38:43,980
I never used to be an addict. I...

587
00:38:47,650 --> 00:38:49,890
Hi, my name is Sara, and I'm an addict.

588
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:51,448
Hi, Sara.

589
00:38:56,770 --> 00:38:58,903
Hi, my name's Lance, and I'm an addict.

590
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,239
Hi, Lance.

591
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:05,668
I guess a lot of what Sara
just said resonates with me

592
00:39:05,762 --> 00:39:07,380
in what I'm going through.

593
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:12,211
Put in all that work,
break out of prison,

594
00:39:12,212 --> 00:39:14,390
only to end up dead
at the bottom of a ditch.

595
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:16,526
Kind of sad really.

596
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:18,782
So, which one of them was it?

597
00:39:22,750 --> 00:39:23,817
Shales.

598
00:39:24,450 --> 00:39:25,471
Shales?

599
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:28,213
S- Scofield. Might be Scofield.

600
00:39:28,410 --> 00:39:31,072
You're probably going
to find his brother in there, too.

601
00:39:32,801 --> 00:39:35,549
Oscar Shales is this guy
Mahone tracked for a while.

602
00:39:35,608 --> 00:39:38,124
Nasty little bottom feeder.
You know the type.

603
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:40,539
He's still in the wind.

604
00:39:40,741 --> 00:39:42,420
Can't get 'em all, right?

605
00:40:06,151 --> 00:40:08,600
We should have a pretty clear path
to Utah now.

606
00:40:09,380 --> 00:40:11,800
They'll turn their attention
to the other guys,

607
00:40:12,100 --> 00:40:14,414
which means we'll be
off their radar for a while.

608
00:40:14,592 --> 00:40:17,243
They're going to get the lab results
back from the accident, man.

609
00:40:17,282 --> 00:40:19,150
We'll be in Mexico by that time.

610
00:40:19,560 --> 00:40:21,460
Provided the transport comes through.

611
00:40:31,294 --> 00:40:32,910
Oh, come on, baby.

612
00:40:44,957 --> 00:40:46,447
<i>In the rainbow room.</i>

613
00:40:48,462 --> 00:40:52,507
<i>Do you remember that beautiful spot
where we took that picture,</i>

614
00:40:52,907 --> 00:40:54,824
<i>the one by the window?</i>

615
00:40:56,693 --> 00:41:01,720
<i>I am going to be waiting
in that spot one week from now.</i>

616
00:41:35,190 --> 00:41:36,507
She sleeping okay?

617
00:41:37,961 --> 00:41:39,993
Yeah. Like a baby.

618
00:41:40,570 --> 00:41:41,673
Good.

619
00:41:42,991 --> 00:41:45,236
So, you said you had some information

620
00:41:45,275 --> 00:41:47,133
you wanted to tell me
about your husband?

621
00:41:58,890 --> 00:42:00,640
Looks like I owe you another one.

622
00:42:01,260 --> 00:42:02,505
It's okay.

623
00:42:04,530 --> 00:42:09,320
Well, uh, once we get to Mexico,
I'll send you $10,000, like I promised.

624
00:42:09,780 --> 00:42:11,660
Plus another three for the car.

625
00:42:12,490 --> 00:42:15,440
Are you meeting up with her, the doctor?

626
00:42:16,070 --> 00:42:17,351
Sara?

627
00:42:20,970 --> 00:42:22,719
I, uh...I... I don't know.

628
00:42:23,193 --> 00:42:25,970
We should get moving.
Next town is a few miles away.

629
00:42:26,536 --> 00:42:28,781
That's fine.
I can catch a bus from there.

630
00:42:30,500 --> 00:42:31,915
Thanks again, Nika.

631
00:42:50,309 --> 00:42:52,709
I knew the little whore
would take us right to 'em.

